Laboratory 7 - Product Inventory API Report
============================================

API ENDPOINT INFORMATION:
-------------------------

1. Complete URL path for POST endpoint:
   POST http://localhost:8080/api/products

2. Complete URL path and expected status code for non-existent item in GET by ID request:
   GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/999
   Expected Status Code: 404 Not Found

3. Successful POST Request Details:
   - Endpoint: POST http://localhost:8080/api/products
   - Expected Status Code: 201 Created
   - Request Body Example:
     {
       "name": "Laptop Pro",
       "price": 1599.99
     }
   - Response Body Example:
     {
       "id": 2,
       "name": "Laptop Pro",
       "price": 1599.99
     }

INITIAL PRODUCT DATA:
--------------------
- ID: 1, Name: Laptop Pro, Price: 1599.99
- ID: 2, Name:
- ID: 3, Name:

API ENDPOINTS SUMMARY:
----------------------
- GET    /api/products           - Get all products (200 OK)
- GET    /api/products/{id}      - Get product by ID (200 OK or 404 Not Found)
- POST   /api/products           - Create new product (201 Created)
- PUT    /api/products/{id}      - Update product (200 OK or 404 Not Found)
- DELETE /api/products/{id}      - Delete product (200 OK or 404 Not Found)
- GET    /api/products/count     - Get total product count (200 OK)

TESTING INSTRUCTIONS:
---------------------
1. Start the Spring Boot application
2. Use Postman or any REST client to test endpoints
3. Application runs on port 8080
4. Base URL: http://localhost:8080